title: For Sale:  Calling All American Patriots
postcontent:
My fellow patriots, today we are on the precipice of a loss of liberty that the generations before us earned by force of arms and defended with their blood.  The liberty at risk is so much greater than merely our individual rights to arms protected under the 2nd Amendment of the United States Constitution; no it is all of the cherished rights granted us under the entirety of the Bill of Rights.  The proposed legislation offered by liberal politicians, elected in regions of this country that clearly do not share in what I believe are the core values of the Midwestern states, and pushed forward under media blanket that is so despicable and devoid of any journalistic integrity as to be merely propaganda, is an effort to undermine the very fabric of our Constitution.

We cannot sit on the sidelines and hope that others will defend our liberties.  I have watched in disgust the attempts to paint the National Rifle Association and law abiding gun owners as the problem.  As a parent, I want to ensure the safety of our children, and abhor the senseless tragedy that occurred in Newton, Connecticut; but that tragedy is only made worse when politicians use it as the supposed “catalyst” for pushing an addenda that has been years in the making and would have been rolled out, regardless, following the November 2012 elections.

Therefore, I call upon those of you who love our rights and freedoms to immediately take peaceful action to defend the 2nd amendment.  Please, if you are not a member of the NRA, spend the $30.00 and join; this fight is too important not to have every gun owner standing side by side in the ranks of patriots, defending our freedoms. 

Then, get involved in the political process and write your elected representatives; tell them that you will not tolerate any lack of support for the 2nd Amendment and demand that they represent your views not those of liberal, anti-gun politicians in states that could not be more different than ours.  

We must Act on our beliefs; but only in a way that demonstrates our courage and commitment to peace and freedom and which reflects the core values that our country has long aspired to demonstrate to the world.  

God Bless and Protect Our United States!
